data.description: 100% USDA Financing available with up to $75,000 in renovation money and no money down with a USDA Renovation Loan! Charming 1927 bungalow, just listed in quaint Campobello, SC is awaiting your renovation!  Sitting atop a nicely terraced lot of .61 acre parcel, you’re going to fall in love with this precious, historic home!  As you approach the home, you’ll notice the long wrap-around porch with columns (perfect for multiple rockers and relaxing while you watch the world go by!)  The nicely sized living room with original wooden panels has lots of large windows and natural light!  As you step toward the back of the home, you’ll find a cozy kitchen that adjoins a spacious dining room, where you will have no problems accommodating large family get-togethers.  This home has a split bedroom plan, with the master and one secondary on one side, that share a bathroom with a walk-in shower! The remaining bedroom is found on the other side of the home and has beadboard siding on the walls (also original to the home) and massive windows as well! As you walk out the back door at the kitchen, you enter a small sun porch with shelving that would be perfect for those indoor plants!  Just a few steps out the door, you can access a storage building that was used in the past for storing the family’s canned foods and as a brooder house for chickens.  There’s plenty of parking to be had here, with a one-car carport and a shed at the back (with additional storage) and spacious enough for at least three vehicles or even to park a tractor or boat!  The landscape is full of mature trees and shrubs, including oaks, two pecan trees, multiple flowering dogwoods, gardenias, and a huge forsythia bush up front!  This sweet home needs TLC, but much of the demo has been done for you.  One look at this home and you’ll immediately envision all the possibilities it has inside!  The larger home next door is currently listed at $420,000, so get in on the ground floor of all the renovations happening in Campobello!
